{{Infobox language |name=Arop-Lokep |region=[[Vitiaz Strait]], [[Papua New Guinea]] |speakers={{sigfig|3015|2}} |date = 2000 census |ref=e18 |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Western Oceanic languages|Western Oceanic]] |fam5=[[Ngero–Vitiaz languages|Ngero–Vitiaz]] |fam6=[[Korap languages|Korap]] |script=[[Latin script|Latin]] |iso3=apr |glotto=arop1243 |glottorefname=Arop-Lokep |notice=IPA }} '''Arop-Lokep''' (also spelled '''Arop-Lukep''') is an [[Oceanic languages|Oceanic language]] spoken by 3,015 people ({{As of|2000|lc=on}}) on four islands in the [[Siassi chain]] in the [[Vitiaz Strait]] in [[Papua New Guinea]].
