{{Infobox language |name=Caquetio |nativename= |region= |states=[[Venezuela]], [[ABC islands (Lesser Antilles)|ABC islands]] |ethnicity=[[Caquetio people]] |extinct=1862, with the death of Nicolaas Pyclas. |ref=<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.namaruba.org/_media/first-inhabitants.pdf# |title=Archived copy |access-date=2014-12-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131013105134/http://www.namaruba.org/_media/first-inhabitants.pdf# |archive-date=2013-10-13 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Maipurean languages|Arawakan]] |fam2 = Northern |fam3 = [[Ta-Arawakan]] |iso3=none |glotto=arub1238 |glottoname=Aruba }}
'''Caquetio''' is an extinct [[Arawakan language]] of [[Venezuela]]. The [[Caquetio people]] lived along the shores of [[Lake Maracaibo]] and on the Dutch 'ABC' islands of [[Aruba]], [[Curaçao]] and [[Bonaire]].
